                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2504.11092/extracted/6362965/figure/pipeline/pipeline.png",
                "caption": "Figure 3:4D reconstruction based on view augmentation.Given an input monocular video, we first perform sparse reconstruction to obtain camera poses and align monocular depth to metric scale, forming an initial data bufferùíü0subscriptùíü0\\mathcal{D}_{0}caligraphic_D start_POSTSUBSCRIPT 0 end_POSTSUBSCRIPT. In each iterative view augmentation step, we select frames at each timestamp from the previous bufferùíüj‚àí1subscriptùíüùëó1\\mathcal{D}_{j-1}caligraphic_D start_POSTSUBSCRIPT italic_j - 1 end_POSTSUBSCRIPTand warp them to novel viewpoints using pre-defined camera posesùêìùêì\\mathbf{T}bold_T, creating new perspective videos with continuous invisible region masks. These masked videos, along with binary masks and an anchor video, are fed into our pre-trained anchor-conditioned video inpainting diffusion model to produce completed novel-view videos. We update the bufferùíüjsubscriptùíüùëó\\mathcal{D}_{j}caligraphic_D start_POSTSUBSCRIPT italic_j end_POSTSUBSCRIPTwith these enhanced videos, their metric depths and poses. Finally, both the original monocular video and all synthesized multi-view videos are used to supervise 4D scene reconstruction.",
                "position": 176
            },
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2504.11092/extracted/6362965/figure/view_augmentation/view_augmentation.png",
                "caption": "Figure 4:Difference between Direct Warping and Iterative Warping.ùíÆùíÆ\\mathcal{S}caligraphic_SandùíØùíØ\\mathcal{T}caligraphic_Tdenote spatial and temporal dimensions, withùí±ùí±\\mathcal{V}caligraphic_Vbeing the input monocular video¬†(yellow dots indicating camera poses in 4D space). Left: WithN=1ùëÅ1N=1italic_N = 1, we directly warp the input video to new perspectives¬†(green dots) in a single iteration. Warped frames are ranked by warping distance per timestamp and organized into a video (purple underline). Right: WithN=2ùëÅ2N=2italic_N = 2, the video is first warped the closest pre-defined poses¬†(green dots,j=1ùëó1j=1italic_j = 1), then additional perspectives¬†(red dots,j=2ùëó2j=2italic_j = 2) are generated by selecting frames with minimal warping angles from existing frames. This iterative approach minimizes distortion and floaters caused by depth inaccuracies in large-angle warping, enhancing reconstruction quality.",
